Comprehensive SEO Strategy for Keyword Grouping and Avoiding Internal Competition Across All Pages
This detailed strategy ensures that our website ranks efficiently for both high-value keywords (e.g., "Red Bandanas") and specific product-related keywords while avoiding internal competition. This involves keyword research, grouping, page segmentation, optimization, and content planning for all categories and product pages on our site.

1. Key Principles for Organizing Keywords and Pages
A. Primary Keyword Grouping Rules
Assign One Main Keyword to Each Page:
 Every page should have a specific focus keyword that doesn’t overlap with other pages.


Example:
Landing Page: "Red Bandanas"
Product Page: "Paisley Red Bandana 22x22"
Categorize Keywords by Intent:


Informational Keywords: Target blogs to attract traffic (e.g., "How to use a red bandana").
Transactional Keywords: Use for product pages or category pages (e.g., "Buy red paisley bandanas").
Navigational Keywords: Focus on brand-related searches (e.g., "Wholesale for Everyone red bandanas").
Map Keywords to Specific Pages:
 Create a keyword-to-page mapping sheet to ensure all keywords are assigned to the right page, avoiding duplication.



B. Content Hierarchy and URL Structure
Organize our content into clear categories, subcategories, and product pages based on keywords:
Category Page/Landing Pages: Optimize for broad, high-volume keywords (e.g., "Bandanas").
URL: /bandanas/
Subcategory Pages: Focus on color, design, or use-specific keywords (e.g., "Red Bandanas").
URL: /bandanas/red-bandanas/
Product Pages: Optimize for long-tail and detailed keywords (e.g., "Paisley Red Bandana 22x22").
URL: /bandanas/red-bandanas/paisley-red-bandana-22x22/

