3. Detailed Strategy for Avoiding Internal Competition
A. Landing Pages
Focus on broad, high-volume keywords related to the category or subcategory.
Use internal links to funnel authority from product pages and blogs to the landing pages.
Example for "Red Bandanas" Landing Page:
Target Keywords:
Primary: "Red Bandanas"
Supporting: "Wholesale Red Bandanas," "Buy Red Bandanas," "Bulk Red Bandanas"
Optimization Checklist:
Title Tag: "Red Bandanas - Wholesale, Bulk & Individual | Wholesale for Everyone"
Meta Description: "Shop premium Red Bandanas in paisley and solid styles. 100% cotton, available individually or in bulk!"
Content:
Showcase popular products with clear links to product pages.
Add sections for FAQs, styling ideas, and material details.

B. Product Pages
Each product page should target a specific, detailed keyword and avoid competing with broader landing pages.
Example for a Product Page: "Paisley Red Bandana 22x22":
Target Keywords:
Primary: "Paisley Red Bandana 22x22"
Supporting: "Cotton Red Paisley Bandana," "Vintage Red Paisley Bandana"
Optimization Checklist:
Title Tag: "Paisley Red Bandana 22x22 - 100% Cotton | Wholesale for Everyone"
Meta Description: "Shop our Paisley Red Bandana, made from premium 100% cotton. Available in bulk or single pieces."
Content:
Highlight the product’s unique features (e.g., material, size, design).
Include internal links to the landing page (e.g., "Explore all our Red Bandanas").

C. Blogs
Blogs should focus on informational keywords that attract users earlier in the buying process. Use blogs to:
Funnel traffic to landing pages through internal linking.
Target long-tail and trend-based keywords.
Example Blog: "How to Style a Red Bandana"
Target Keywords:
Primary: "How to Style a Red Bandana"
Supporting: "Bandana Styling Tips," "Red Bandana Fashion Ideas"
Optimization Checklist:
Include internal links:
"Looking to buy one? Check out our collection of Red Bandanas."
Create visual content: Add images of styled bandanas with alt text targeting keywords.

D. Internal Linking Structure
Landing Pages:
Link from blogs and product pages using anchor text targeting the primary keyword.
Product Pages:
Link back to landing pages to funnel authority.
Example: "Looking for more styles? Explore our full collection of Red Bandanas."
Blogs:
Include links to both landing pages and product pages.

E. Technical SEO Adjustments
Canonical Tags:


Use canonical tags on product pages to point to the landing page for similar keywords.
Example: A product page for "Paisley Red Bandana" can have a canonical tag pointing to /red-bandanas/.
Noindex Tags:


Use noindex for thin or duplicate content pages (e.g., filtered product lists).
Structured Data:


Add schema markup to enhance visibility in search results for product and category pages.

